Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} lengthways. Quarter any larger pieces.

On a lined #baking tray{}, toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a
drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer, cut-side down.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Remove from the oven and lightly crush each potato with the bottom of a pan.
Drizzle with more oil and return to the top shelf until crispy and golden,
~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with @butter{to taste}.

When melted, add @flour{to taste} then slowly stir in @water{to taste}.

Bring to the boil, stirring, then simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix in the @creme fraiche{65%g} and @grated cheese{50%g}. Stir until all the
cheese has melted.

Remove from the heat, stir through the @chipotle paste{1%sachet} and season to
taste with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Season the @21 day aged Irish sirloin steak{250%g} with salt and pepper.

Once the pan is hot, fry until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it more well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.
> Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover and allow to rest.

Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with another drizzle of oil if required.

Once hot, fry the green beans until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Thinly slice the steaks widthways.

Gently reheat the chipotle cheese sauce, if necessary.

Divide the smashed potatoes between plates.

Serve the pan-fried green beans and sliced sirloin alongside.

Drizzle the chipotle cheese sauce over the steak.

Serve any remaining sauce on the side.